headlines.description: — Zach LaVine continued his strong play with 25 points and nine assists, leading the Chicago Bulls to a 123-110 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine continues strong play, leads Bulls past Hornets

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant's driving layup on the final play came too late, and the Houston Rockets held on for a 103-102 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets withstand final review in 103-102 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogdon hit the decisive 3-pointer with 2.8 seconds left in overtime, lifting the Indiana Pacers to a 120-118 win over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brogdon's 3-pointer lifts Pacers past Magic 120-118 in OT

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton had 25 points and nine assists, Andre Drummond added 19 points and 16 rebounds and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Brooklyn Nets for the second time in three days, 125-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 25, Cavaliers beat Durant-less Nets 125-113

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 38 points and 11 rebounds, Tobias Harris scored 23 points and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Boston Celtics 122-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid dominates again in 76ers' 122-110 win over Celtics

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 23 points, OG Anunoby added 21 and the Toronto Raptors recovered in the second half after blowing a 21-point lead to beat the Miami Heat 101-81 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell, Raptors regroup after blowing lead, beat Heat 101-81

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored a season-high 43 points, Clint Capela had 13 points, 19 rebounds and 10 blocks, and the Atlanta Hawks topped the Minnesota Timberwolves 116-98 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 43, Capela nets triple-double in Hawks' win

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 36 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks withstood a late rally to beat the San Antonio Spurs 122-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavericks fend off late rally to beat Spurs, 122-107

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 31 points, Gary Harris added 19 and the Denver Nuggets rallied to force overtime before beating the Phoenix Suns 130-126 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 31, Nuggets rally to beat Suns 130-126 in OT

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 31 points, Paul George added 29 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 120-106 on Friday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers dominate, beat Thunder 120-106 for 6th win in row

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers
New York Knicks at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes had 21 points, eight rebounds and seven assists, and the Sacramento Kings overcame a cold shooting spell late in the fourth quarter to hold off the New York Knicks 103-94 on Friday night and end a four-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings overcome late cold spell to beat Knicks 103-94
